        <content><![CDATA[<p>We only mention relevant components.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="%(link0)">See here to get an overview on tested software versions.</a></li>
</ul>
<p>In essence, to run OpenCms you need:</p>
<ul>
<li>A <strong>Java Development Kit</strong>: OpenCms requires JDK 8 or higher.
<ul>
<li><a href="%(link1)">List of compatible JDKs</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>A <strong>servlet container</strong>: OpenCms runs as servlet in a servlet container. We recommend <strong>Apache Tomcat</strong>.
<ul>
<li><a href="%(link2)">List of compatible servlet containers</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>A <strong>database management system</strong>: OpenCms stores all content in a database. It is best tested with MySql/MariaDB. But also other databases are supported.
<ul>
<li><a href="%(link3)">List of compatible database management systems</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>]]></content>
